  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "31:1-11 The Israelites, who had been masons and bricklayers in Egypt, were not qualified for curious workmanship; but the Spirit who gave the apostles utterance in divers tongues, miraculously gave Bezaleel and Aholiab the skill that was wanting. The honour which comes from God, is always attended with a work to be done; to be employed for God is high honour. Those whom God calls to any service, he will find or make fit for it. The Lord gives different gifts to different persons; let each mind his proper work, diligently remembering that whatever wisdom any one possesses, the Lord put it in the heart, to do his commandments.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And the cloths of service - Rather, And the garments of office; that is, the distinguishing official garments of the high priest. The three kinds of dress mentioned in this verse appear to be the only ones which were unique to the sanctuary. They were:",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(1) The richly adorned state robes of the high priest (see Exodus 28:6-38; Exodus 39:1 following).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(1) The richly adorned state robes of the high priest (see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Exodus 28:6-38",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Exodus 39:1",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " following).",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(2) the \"holy garments\" of white linen for the high priest, worn on the most solemn occasion in the year (see Exodus 28:39; Leviticus 16:4).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(2) the \"holy garments\" of white linen for the high priest, worn on the most solemn occasion in the year (see ",
            "children": []
          },
